  "prompt": "How do you drop off a U-Haul at a different location?",
  "response": "To drop off a U-Haul at a different location (one-way rental):\n\n1. When you initially rent the truck, specify the different drop-off location during the reservation process.\n\n2. Pay the one-way rental fee, which covers the cost of returning the truck to a different location.\n\n3. Check your rental agreement for the specific drop-off location and time.\n\n4. Ensure the truck is returned:\n- With the agreed-upon fuel level\n- Clean inside and out\n- With all equipment and accessories\n\n5. At the drop-off location:\n- Park in the designated U-Haul return area\n- Remove all personal items\n- Check in with the location's staff\n- Complete any necessary paperwork\n- Return the keys\n\n6. Get a final receipt and confirm the return is complete\n\nNote: One-way rental fees vary depending on the distance between pickup and drop-off locations, truck size, and current demand. It's best to confirm specific details with U-Haul when making your reservation.",
